Goal:
Exercise all the Cooperative Tensor Load flavours explained in PRM-10, including the TensorLoad TenB and the ilegal transformations. This version only cooperates with minions of the Neigh0.

Details:
The test only runs in thread 0 of each minion. The test does a 'for' loop (size of the loop can be controlled with the 'LOOP_SIZE' define).
For each loop iteration, a different tensor load flavour is executed and there is no tensor waits within the loop to stress the implicit dependency between consecutive tensor loads.
If the 'SELF_CHECK' variable is set, each tensor load operation is self-checked* following these steps:
   1) Tensor Wait to make sure the previous operation is done
   2) Dump the whole L1SCP content in a memory region (stack)
   3) Execute the Tensor Load operation
   4) Tensor Wait to make sure the current operation is done
   5) Dump the whole L1SCP content in a memory region (stack)
   6) Model the Tensor Load behaviour using RISC-V basic instructions.
        - This model will perform the same loads as the Tensor Load operation into the memory region from 2)
        - Will compare the modified memory content from 2) against the memory content from 5). These two regions must contain the exact same data.

* The Tensor Load TenB operation cannot be self-checked without self-checking the TFMA operation that pairs it. For this tests, only non-tenb operations will be self-checked.
